│   Rationale: This prevents the first transformation from swapping in a        │
│ shufflevector that leads to reconstructing both lanes with sext. It adheres   │
│ to correctness by keeping the original non-vectorized scalar ops (zext/sext)  │
│ intact.                                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ - Edit Point 2 (alternate extension cost block):                              │
│   Lines 11290-11341 in llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp.       │
│   Strengthen the cost model to return a high cost (or early-return without    │
│ profit) when encountering alternating integer extensions where the scalar     │
│ element type width comparison indicates a truncation pattern. Specifically,   │
│ after logging "alternate extension, which should be truncated.", make the     │
│ vectorization path bail out if the alternation is between sext and zext and   │
│ the emission path cannot preserve per-lane signedness.                        │
│                                                                               │
│   Rationale: This aligns the profitability decision with the conservative     │
│ semantics guard, avoiding contradictions between cost model and legality and  │
│ preventing the vectorizer from choosing an unsafe transformation.             │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The bug arises because the tiny-tree vectorization path for alternating       │
│ extension ops loses per-lane signedness, converting a zero-extend into a      │
│ sign-extend. This is correctness-critical under Alive2 and wraps flags. The   │
│ proposed fix conservatively prevents vectorization of such mixed sext/zext    │
│ tiny trees by (a) rejecting vectorization in getScalarsVectorizationState for │
│ extract sequences feeding alternating integer extensions with different       │
│ signedness, and (b) ensuring the cost model does not prefer this              │
│ transformation when alternation suggests truncation. This keeps the IR        │
│ semantically equivalent and avoids poisoning, until a more robust emission    │
│ that preserves per-lane extension opcodes is implemented.                     │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
