│ The previous attempts introduced broad guards that impacted many SLP tests.   │
│ To minimally fix the reported miscompile while preserving existing            │
│ vectorization behavior, I implemented narrowly-scoped checks that only bail   │
│ out for the tiny-tree case that causes the poison mismatch.                   │
│                                                                               │
│ Summary of the final changes:                                                 │
│ - In getScalarsVectorizationState for ExtractElement: Added a conservative    │
│ check only when:                                                              │
│   - We are reusing a pair of extracts (VL.size() == 2, Reuse == true).        │
│   - Each extract has exactly one integer extension user, and the two users    │
│ are one sext and one zext to the same integer destination type.               │
│   - These two extended values are directly consumed together by an add        │
│ instruction carrying nsw or nuw.                                              │
│   - The source types of the extensions are non-i1 integers (to avoid breaking │
│ mask/vector-predicate related tests).                                         │
│   In that specific case, return NeedToGather to avoid emitting the unsafe     │
│ shuffle+uniform-sext pattern.                                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ - In the cast-handling case for alternate-op bundles: Added a similar         │
│ narrowly-scoped guard. Only bail out if the alt bundle is sext/zext of the    │
│ same destination integer type and the two extended values are directly        │
│ consumed together by a nowrap add, and both source types are non-i1 integers. │
│                                                                               │
│ - Removed earlier broad guards that caused test regressions, keeping the      │
│ checks targeted and conditional on the precise pattern that leads to the      │
│ Alive2-poison mismatch in the reproducer.                                     │
│                                                                               │
│ This approach fixes the original bug without affecting other platforms/tests  │
│ that rely on vectorizing mixed sext/zext patterns for i1 masks or where no    │
│ nowrap add directly consumes the extended values together.                    │
